author: Joaquin Palomino
title: Thousands expected to descend on S.F. for Oracle’s OpenWorld
text:
Photo: Scott Strazzante, The Chronicle Oracle OpenWorld attendees populate the Moscone Convention Center in San Francisco, Calif. on Wednesday, October 1, 2014. Oracle OpenWorld attendees populate the Moscone Convention Center...
An estimated 60,000 people will stream into San Francisco this week for Oracle’s OpenWorld conference, a tech gathering that runs Sunday through Thursday and has a speaker lineup including Intel CEO Brian Krzanich and Golden State Warriors President and Chief Operating Officer Rick Welts.
